cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.AI

This paper deals with machine learning and fairness in high-stakes decision-making, which suggests it could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The specific focus on predictive risk scores in criminal justice and other domains suggests it could also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the use of metrics and analysis techniques suggests it could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
